{
  "doc_id": "31955",
  "text": "The divergent thinking test battery consisted of three alternate uses tasks and three instances tasks [CITATION_1] . The alternate uses tasks required participants to generate creative uses for three common objects: a can, a knife, and a hairdryer. The instances tasks required participants to generate creative solutions to the three problems: What can make noise?, What can be elastic?, and What can be used for speedy travel?",
